{"title_page": "Patrick Proisy", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=June 2013}}\n{{Infobox tennis biography\n| name                  = Patrick Proisy\n| fullname               =\n| image                 = File:Internationale tennistoernooi Melkhuisje finale Patrick Proisy in actie, Bestanddeelnr 929-2710.jpg\n| country               = {{FRA}}\n| residence             = Paris, France\n| birth_date             = {{birth date and age|df=yes|1949|9|10}}\n| birth_place            = [[Evreux]], France\n| height                = {{height|m=1.80}}\n| turnedpro             = 1968\n| retired               = 1981\n| plays                 = Right-handed (one-handed backhand)\n| careerprizemoney      =\n| singlesrecord         = 200\u2013176<small> (Open era)\n| singlestitles         = 2\n| highestsinglesranking = No. 16 (23 October 1972)\n| AustralianOpenresult  = SF ([[1973 Australian Open \u2013 Men's Singles|1973]])\n| FrenchOpenresult      = F ([[1972 French Open \u2013 Men's Singles|1972]])\n| Wimbledonresult       = 2R ([[1971 Wimbledon Championships \u2013 Men's Singles|1971]], [[1972 Wimbledon Championships \u2013 Men's Singles|1972]], [[1974 Wimbledon Championships \u2013 Men's Singles|1974]])\n| USOpenresult          = 2R ([[1972 US Open \u2013 Men's Singles|1972]], [[1977 US Open \u2013 Men's Singles|1977]])\n| doublesrecord         = 72\u2013120 <small>(Open era)\n| doublestitles         =\n| highestdoublesranking =\n| AustralianOpenDoublesresult  =\n| FrenchOpenDoublesresult      =\n| WimbledonDoublesresult       =\n| USOpenDoublesresult          =\n| awards                = \n| medaltemplates-expand    = yes\n| medaltemplates = \n{{MedalCountry | {{FRA}}}}\n{{MedalSport|Men's [[Tennis]]}}\n{{MedalCompetition | [[Summer Universiade]]}}\n{{MedalGold|[[Tennis at the 1970 Summer Universiade|1970 Turin]]|Singles}}\n}}\n\n'''Patrick Proisy''' (born 10 September 1949) is a French former professional [[tennis]] player best remembered for reaching the final of the French Open in 1972<ref name=\"Djata2008\">{{cite book|last=Djata|first=Sundiata A.|title=Blacks at the net: Black achievement in the history of tennis|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=5dHCPTSl7-sC&pg=PA5|accessdate=16 March 2011|date=March 2008|publisher=Syracuse University Press|isbn=978-0-8156-0898-1|pages=5\u2013}}</ref><ref name=\"CollinsHollander1994\">{{cite book|last1=Collins|first1=Bud|last2=Hollander|first2=Zander|title=Bud Collins' modern encyclopedia of tennis|url=https://archive.org/details/budcollinsmodern00coll|url-access=registration|accessdate=16 March 2011|year=1994|publisher=Gale Research|isbn=978-0-8103-8988-5|page=[https://archive.org/details/budcollinsmodern00coll/page/424 424]}}</ref> (where he beat top seed and defending champion [[Jan Kodes]] in the quarter finals and fourth seed [[Manuel Orantes]] in the semi finals before losing the final against sixth seeded Spaniard [[Andr\u00e9s Gimeno]] in four sets).<ref name=\"gsta\">{{cite web|title=French Open 1972|url=http://www.tennis.co.nf/FRENCH%20OPEN%201972.htm|website=www.tennis.co.nf}}</ref>  He added to that one more final (in [[Florence]], 1976) and singles titles in [[Priority Telecom Open|Hilversum]], 1977 and [[Perth, Western Australia|Perth]], 1972. Proisy reached a career-high singles ranking of World No. 16 in October 1972.\n\n==Grand Slam finals==\n\n===Singles (1 runner-up)===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!style=\"width:70px\"|Outcome\n!style=\"width:50x\"|Year\n!style=\"width:180px\"|Championship\n!style=\"width:180px\"|Opponent\n!style=\"width:160px\" class=\"unsortable\"|Score\n|-bgcolor=\"#EBC2AF\"\n| style=\"background:#FFA07A\" | Runner-up||1972 || French Open || {{flagicon|ESP|1945}} [[Andr\u00e9s Gimeno]] || 6\u20134, 3\u20136, 1\u20136, 1\u20136\n|}\n\n==Grand Slam tournament performance timeline==\n{{performance key|short=yes|active=no}}\n===Singles===\n{|class=wikitable style=text-align:center\n!Tournament !!1968 !!1969 !![[1970 Grand Prix (tennis)|1970]] !![[1971 Grand Pri