olicyFocus138_Smyth-2.pdf|title=THE SHIITE JIHAD IN SYRIA AND ITS REGIONAL EFFECTS|publisher=|access-date=2015-06-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150713052402/https://www.washingtoninstitute.org/uploads/Documents/pubs/PolicyFocus138_Smyth-2.pdf|archive-date=2015-07-13|url-status=live}}</ref> one member of the Lebanese [[Amal Movement]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.yalibnan.com/2013/04/08/more-hezbollah-fighters-killed-in-syria-to-be-buried-in-lebanon/ |title=More Hezbollah fighters killed in Syria buried in Lebanon |location=LB |publisher=Yalibnan.com |date=2013-04-08 |accessdate=2013-08-30 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131102141100/http://www.yalibnan.com/2013/04/08/more-hezbollah-fighters-killed-in-syria-to-be-buried-in-lebanon/ |archive-date=2013-11-02 |url-status=live }}</ref> and a Saudi Shiite fighter.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.washingtoninstitute.org/uploads/Documents/pubs/PolicyFocus138_Smyth-2.pdf|title=THE SHIITE JIHAD IN SYRIA AND ITS REGIONAL EFFECTS|publisher=|accessdate=19 February 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190330143415/https://www.washingtoninstitute.org/uploads/Documents/pubs/PolicyFocus138_Smyth-2.pdf|archive-date=30 March 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> Other sources put the overall number of killed Iranian-lead forces, which also includes the Afghan and Pakistani militias,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://english.alarabiya.net/en/News/middle-east/2016/11/14/Tens-of-Iranians-Pakistanis-and-Afghans-killed-in-Syria-battles.html|title=Tens of Iranians, Pakistanis and Afghans killed in Syria battles|publisher=|access-date=2016-11-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161122155715/http://english.alarabiya.net/en/News/middle-east/2016/11/14/Tens-of-Iranians-Pakistanis-and-Afghans-killed-in-Syria-battles.html|archive-date=2016-11-22|url-status=live}}</ref> at between 2,500 and 3,500 by the end of August 2017.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.shahidnews.com/view/170974/\u0628\u0627\u0632\u0633\u0627\u0632\u06cc-\u0648\u0627\u0642\u0639\u0647-\u063a\u062f\u06cc\u0631\u062e\u0645-\u062f\u0631-144-\u0646\u0642\u0637\u0647-\u0627\u0632-\u0627\u06cc\u0631\u0627\u0646-\u0648-\u0633\u0648\u0631\u06cc\u0647- |title=\u0628\u0627\u0632\u0633\u0627\u0632\u06cc \u0648\u0627\u0642\u0639\u0647 \u063a\u062f\u06cc\u0631\u062e\u0645 \u062f\u0631 144 \u0646\u0642\u0637\u0647 \u0627\u0632 \u0627\u06cc\u0631\u0627\u0646 \u0648 \u0633\u0648\u0631\u06cc\u0647 |access-date=2019-12-30 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181008095925/http://www.shahidnews.com/view/170974/\u0628\u0627\u0632\u0633\u0627\u0632\u06cc-\u0648\u0627\u0642\u0639\u0647-\u063a\u062f\u06cc\u0631\u062e\u0645-\u062f\u0631-144-\u0646\u0642\u0637\u0647-\u0627\u0632-\u0627\u06cc\u0631\u0627\u0646-\u0648-\u0633\u0648\u0631\u06cc\u0647- |archive-date=2018-10-08 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://eldorar.com/node/114111|title=\u0639\u0645\u064a\u062f \u0625\u064a\u0631\u0627\u0646\u064a \u064a\u0643\u0634\u0641 \u0639\u0646 \u0625\u062d\u0635\u0627\u0626\u064a\u0629 \u0628\u0623\u0639\u062f\u0627\u062f \u0642\u062a\u0644\u0649 \u0628\u0644\u0627\u062f\u0647 \u0641\u064a \u0633\u0648\u0631\u064a\u0627|first=\u0645\u062d\u0631\u0631 \u0627\u0644\u062f\u0631\u0631|last=\u0627\u0644\u0634\u0627\u0645\u064a\u0629|date=30 August 2017|website=\u0627\u0644\u062f\u0631\u0631 \u0627\u0644\u0634\u0627\u0645\u064a\u0629|accessdate=19 February 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190207125305/https://eldorar.com/node/114111|archive-date=7 February 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> Also, 1,858 Palestinian militiamen have been killed, according to the [[Popular Front for the Liberation of Palestine \u2013 General Command|PFLP\u2013GC]], and these include: 1,100 [[Liwa Al-Quds]] fighters, 400 PFLP\u2013GC members, 285 members of the [[Palestine Liberation Army|PLA]], 42 who belonged to [[Fatah al-Intifada]], 11 [[Palestinian Popular Struggle Front|PPSF]] members, 10 Al Saeka Brigade fighters and 10 [[Free Palestine Movement]] members.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.actionpal.org.uk/en/post/8745/flash-news/talal-naji-over-400-members-of-pflp-gc-killed-in-war-torn-syria|title=Talal Naji: Over 400 Members of PFLP-GC Killed in War-Torn Syria|publisher=Action Group for Palestinians of Syria|accessdate=9 June 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190710205615/http://www.actionpal.org.uk/en/post/8745/flash-news/talal-naji-over-400-members-of-pflp-gc-killed-in-war-torn-syria|archive-date=10 July 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> Additionally, the ''Action Group For Palestinians of Syria'' reported 21 [[Galilee Forces]] fighters had been killed and put the number of dead Free Palestine Movement members higher at 24.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://actionpal.co.uk/en/post/8330/flash-news/728-palestinian-refugees-killed-in-pro-gov-t-shootouts-in-syria|title=728 Palestinian Refugees Killed in Pro-Gov\u2019t Shootouts in Syria|publisher=Action Group for Palestinians of Syria|accessdate=20 February 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190710202857/http://actionpal.co.uk/en/post/8330/flash-news/728-palestinian-refugees-killed-in-pro-gov-t-shootouts-in-syria|archive-date=10 July 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> 17 PLA soldiers were also missing.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.actionpal.org.uk/en/post/8849/flash-news/agps-17-pla-gunmen-missing-in-syria-since-2011 |title=AGPS: 17 PLA Gunmen Missing in Syria since 2011 |access-date=2019-07-10 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190710203023/http://www.actionpal.org.uk/en/post/8849/flash-news/agps-17-pla-gunmen-missing-in-syria-since-2011 |archive-date=2019-07-10 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nExcept one death (August 2011),<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.terrorism-info.org.il/en/article/20521 |title=Hezbollah Involvement in the Syrian Civil War |publisher=Terrorism-info.org.il |date= |accessdate=2013-08-30 |archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/6HrbG8GWu?url=http://www.terrorism-info.org.il/en/article/20521 |archive-date=2013-07-04 |url-status=live }}</ref> all of the Hezbollah fatalities have occurred since September 2012.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.middle-east-online.com/english/?id=58957 |title=Syria drags Lebanon into another Lebanese-Lebanese war |publisher=Middle-east-online.com |date=2013-05-23 |accessdate=2013-08-30 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131106013201/http://www.middle-east-online.com/english/?id=58957 |archive-date=2013-11-06 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nBetween October 2015 and December 2017, it was reported that 150\u2013200 Russian [[Private military company|security contractors]] had been killed.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thedailybeast.com/a-russian-blackwater-putins-secret-soldiers-in-ukraine-and-syria|title=A Russian Blackwater? Putin\u2019s Secret Soldiers in Ukraine and Syria|first=Anna|last=Nemtsova|date=2 January 2018|publisher=|accessdate=20 January 2018|via=www.thedailybeast.com|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180103052420/https://www.thedailybeast.com/a-russian-blackwater-putins-secret-soldiers-in-ukraine-and-syria|archive-date=3 January 2018|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.inopressa.ru/article/14Dec2017/spiegel/vagner01.html|title=\u0420\u043e\u0441\u0441\u0438\u044f \u0441\u043a\u0440\u044b\u0432\u0430\u0435\u0442 \u0443\u0431\u0438\u0442\u044b\u0445|website=www.inopressa.ru|accessdate=20 January 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180122073023/https://www.inopressa.ru/article/14dec2017/spiegel/vagner01.html|archive-date=22 January 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> According to the Syrian Observatory for Human Rights, 264 Russian soldiers and mercenaries were killed until the end of 2019.<ref name=SOHR2/>\n\nIn addition, 1,000 civilian government officials have also been killed.<ref name=\"safepassage\">{{cite web|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.co.uk/2012/11/06/syria-cameron-safe-passage-assad_n_2081341.html|title=David Cameron Offers 'Safe Passage' For Syria's Bashar Al-Assad, But Not To Britain (PICTURES)|work=Huffington Post|date=6 November 2012|accessdate=17 December 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121110064454/http://www.huffingtonpost.co.uk/2012/11/06/syria-cameron-safe-passage-assad_n_2081341.html|archive-date=10 November 2012|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n===Anti-government forces===\n\nDue to the main opposition monitor SOHR's policy early in the conflict of counting rebel fighters that were not defectors as civilians,<ref name=morethan13000/><ref name=\"violence\"/><ref name=over14400/><ref>{{Cite journal | last1 = Al-Gharbi | first1 = M. | doi = 10.1111/mepo.12003 | title = Syria Contextualized: The Numbers Game | journal = Middle East Policy | volume = 20 | pages = 56\u201367 | year = 2013 | pmid =  | pmc = }}</ref> a comprehensive number of rebels killed in the conflict, thus far, has not been ascertained. In late November 2012, SOHR estimated that at least 10,000 rebels had been killed, but noted the possibility of the figure being higher because the rebels, like the government, were lying about how many of their forces had died to make it look like they were winning.<ref name=\"over40000\">{{cite web |author=Reuters |url=http://www.jpost.com/MiddleEast/Article.aspx?id=293186 |title='Over 40,000 killed since start of Syria conflict' |publisher=Jpost.com |date=2012-11-23 |accessdate=2013-08-30 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130513214927/http://www.jpost.com/MiddleEast/Article.aspx?id=293186 |archive-date=2013-05-13 |url-status=live }}</ref> In March 2013, SOHR stated that the actual number of killed rebels and government forces could be double the number they were already able to document.<ref name=SOHRface>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/syriahroe/posts/368424863265858|title=More than 80 thousand people killed since the beginning of the Syrian uprising|publisher=SOHR|accessdate=12 May 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160203164132/https://www.facebook.com/syriahroe/posts/368424863265858|archive-date=3 February 2016|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Anti-government combatants\n! Casualties\n|-\n|'''TOTAL'''\n|'''137,829\u2013193,829''' killed<ref name=SOHR/><ref name=SOHR1/>\n|-\n|[[Islamic State of Iraq and the Levant|ISIL]]\n|'''39,718''' killed\n|-\n|[[Syrian Democratic Forces|SDF]] ([[Syrian Kurdistan|Kurdish]] [[People's Protection Units|YPG]]/[[Women's Protection Units|YPJ]])\n|'''12,111\u201313,624''' killed<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.kurdistan24.net/en/news/0dafe596-6536-49d7-8e23-e52821742ae9|title=SDF says over 11,000 of its forces killed in fight against the Islamic State|author=Wladimir van Wilgenburg|publisher=Kurdistan24|accessdate=23 March 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190330095030/http://www.kurdistan24.net/en/news/0dafe596-6536-49d7-8e23-e52821742ae9|archive-date=30 March 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>[https://www.ypgrojava.org/2017-Balance-Sheet-of-War-%E2%80%93-Syrian-Democratic-Forces 2017 Balance Sheet of War \u2013 Syrian Democratic Forces]<br>[https://www.ypgrojava.org/Results-of-battles-and-resistance-of-YPG-throughout-2018 Results of battles and resistance of YPG throughout 2018]<br>[https://anfenglish.com/rojava-syria/sdf-balance-sheet-of-war-and-resistance-for-2019-40551 SDF balance sheet of war and resistance for 2019]</ref><ref name=SOHR/>\n|}\n\nThere have been 68,226 [[Foreign rebel fighters in the Syrian Civil War|foreign rebel, ISIL and SDF fighters]],<ref name=SOHR/> at least 455 anti-government suicide bombers<ref>1 bomber in 2011,[https://www.mcclatchydc.com/news/nation-world/world/article24758767.html] 103 bombers in 2012-13,[https://www.jpost.com/Syria/Suicide-terrorism-thriving-in-Syria-is-threat-to-West-Israel-new-report-warns-341087] 41 bombings in 2014,[https://www.timesofisrael.com/450-of-452-suicide-attacks-in-2015-were-by-muslim-extremists-study-shows/] 61 bombers in 2015 (download and see full list),[https://www.inss.org.il/publication/suicide-attacks-in-2015/] 55 bombings in 2016,[https://canadafreepress.com/article/suicide-attacks-in-2016-the-highest-number-of-fatalities] 70 bombers in 2017 (download and see full list),[https://www.inss.org.il/publication/report-suicide-attacks-2017-fewer-attacks-women/] 63 bombers in 2018 (download and see full list),[https://www.inss.org.il/publication/suicide-attacks-2018-fewer-attacks-victims-fewer-countries/] 49 bombers in 2019 (download and see full list),[https://www.inss.org.il/publication/suicide-bombings-worldwide-in-2019-signs-of-decline-following-the-military-defeat-of-the-islamic-state/] 12 bombers in Jan.-Feb. 2020,[https://www.longwarjournal.org/archives/2020/02/hts-utilizes-suicide-bombings-against-advancing-regime-forces.php] total of at least 455 suicide bombers killed</ref> and 246 rebel [[Military use of children|child soldiers]]<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.hrw.org/news/2014/06/22/syria-armed-groups-send-children-battle |title=Syria: Armed Groups Send Children into Battle |publisher=HRW |date=2014-06-22 |accessdate=2015-04-18 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150415070738/http://www.hrw.org/news/2014/06/22/syria-armed-groups-send-children-battle |archive-date=2015-04-15 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.alaraby.co.uk/english/news/2015/7/15/syrias-kurdish-militia-still-using-child-soldiers|title=Dozens of IS group child soldiers killed in Syria|author=Al-Araal-Jadeed staff|work=alaraby|accessdate=28 October 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160203164133/http://www.alaraby.co.uk/english/news/2015/7/15/syrias-kurdish-militia-still-using-child-soldiers|archive-date=3 February 2016|url-status=live}}</ref> that have been killed in the conflict. Additionally, 930 foreign pro-Kurdish fighters died.<ref>http://www.syriahr.com/en/?p=152189</ref><ref name=YPGforeigners>26 Turks,[https://now.mmedia.me/lb/en/NewsReports/565298-outlawed-turkish-party-establishes-syria-battalion] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170730212802/https://now.m