7134246/http://www.rbc.ru/rbcfreenews/5a01a0329a79474ee42a1a3c|archive-date=7 November 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> 403\u2013453 Frenchmen,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/wires/afp/article-5185335/Islamic-State-What-happened-foreign-fighters.html|title=Islamic State: What happened to all the foreign fighters?|accessdate=17 December 2017}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.apnews.com/d642d0a72a6e4cb4a5e67420fc895508 |title=Prominent French jihadis killed in IS-held area in Syria |access-date=2019-03-05 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190305213742/https://apnews.com/d642d0a72a6e4cb4a5e67420fc895508 |archive-date=2019-03-05 |url-status=live }}</ref> 400 Turks,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://en.alalam.ir/news/1739939|title=More Than 1,200 Turks Fighting in Iraq & Syria, 400 Killed So-Far|date=18 September 2015|work=Al-Alam|accessdate=18 September 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150920061935/http://en.alalam.ir/news/1739939|archive-date=20 September 2015|url-status=live}}</ref> 300 Azerbaijanis,<ref>900 went to Syria and Iraq, of which 300 were killed in Iraq and 280 were arrested or stripped of citizenship,[https://www.iraqinews.com/iraq-war/azerbaijan-probes-300-killed-iraq-holds-21-foreign-children/] with most of the remainder (320) killed in Syria [https://www.almasdarnews.com/article/900-azerbaijanis-joined-terrorist-groups-syria-iraq-now-dead/]</ref> 300 Tajiks,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://en.farsnews.com/newstext.aspx?nn=13940903000607|title=Farsnews|publisher=|accessdate=12 April 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160203164134/http://en.farsnews.com/newstext.aspx?nn=13940903000607|archive-date=3 February 2016|url-status=live}}</ref> 220\u2013380 Germans,<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.dw.com/en/germany-loses-track-of-160-islamic-state-supporters/a-49317535|title=Germany loses track of 160 'Islamic State' supporters|date=2019-06-23|work=Deutsche Welle|access-date=2019-06-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/